&gt; Tucson had seen complex strategies before and this one was definitely trying
&gt; everyone&#39;s logic circuits.  Military strategy was one of his areas of
&gt; expertise and it was a good opportunity to exercise his skills as a
&gt; strategist.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; before I evolved into a Prime, I spent quite a few vorns assisting the
&gt; Autobots in the military strategy department.  And this one here, is very
&gt; much like something I&#39;ve seen before.  Not by Unicronians but by the
&gt; Decepticons back in the days of the wars on Iacon.  I was only a rookie at
&gt; the time but I&#39;ve always had a knack in this field of study so the officers
&gt; gave me a chance to attempt to crack a very complex case.  It had to do with
&gt; how they were causing Autobots to vanish on the battlefield.  As everything
&gt; is now it was back then.  They vanished in various quadrants and when I used
&gt; a holographic map and drew lines that connected those locations, it came up
&gt; with an epicenter of activity around the drawn lines.  I told the officers I
&gt; wasn&#39;t a hundred percent sure but it was possible that the location was the
&gt; area we were looking for.  They investigated and they found the missing
&gt; Autobots housed in an abandoned complex on Cybertron.   It was one of
&gt; Shockwave&#39;s master plans that were intended to remain a mystery but he did
&gt; not count on a not so average Autobot to figure it out.  I was always
&gt; considered to be a bit strange, and off the beaten path.  But the council
&gt; kept me on their team all the same.  They said due to my rebel like nature,
&gt; that I would not be chosen as a commander but my skills were a great asset
&gt; to them.  I was content with their decision all the same.  I was comfortable
&gt; just being who I was.  So if I&#39;m not a good fit as a Prime, I respect their
&gt; decision. &quot;
&gt;
&gt; He returns to robot mode.  He looks to Leo Prime with a strategists
&gt; expression.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; I may be wrong about my theory but I&#39;m curious to see if this case is
&gt; similar to the one I decoded back on Cybertron.   And if it is, we could
&gt; even locate the purpetrator as well.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was an answering nod from LEO PRIME. &quot;Of course and I have seen
the recordings of that stratagy. What Shockwave was doing could be
called a feint. He gave you something to be figured out, and yet it
was destract you from his more important goal.&quot;
LEO FROWNED, &quot;Something that may be happening here.&quot; He looked at
TUSCON as he spoke, &quot;But from what Wing Caliber tells me though is
that it did save them a lot of time which was useful in defeating
SHockwave.&quot;

The screen changed as LEO entered the parameters that were known. The
approximate place where CHEETOR was last seen as well as CYCLONUS and
RODIMUS. &quot;Interesting.&quot; LEO said. &quot;It does seem that these soldiers
were all captured in a similar location, within perhaps several
hundred miles from each other.&quot;

Plugging the information on the screen the picture of that same jungle
appeared again. &quot;It would seem that this same location is still being
pointed to.&quot; There was a slight shrug, &quot;But without knowing where
Primal was when he was taken it is hard to hazzard a guess.&quot;

LEO looked up at TUSCON, &quot;Didn&#39;t the last report about Cheetor&#39;s
captors say that they were Minion or at least the readings showed
minion energy in use?&quot; He nodded as he stroked his chin thoughtfully.

